Map showing Count of Listing Type by Nerighbourhood¶

In [39]:
a=pd.DataFrame(listings_summary.groupby(["neighbourhood","room_type"]).size())

a=a.reset_index()

b=pd.DataFrame(listings_summary.groupby(["neighbourhood"]).size())

b=b.reset_index()

t=pd.merge(a,b,how='outer',on='neighbourhood')

t=t.rename(columns={'0_x':"listing_number","0_y":"total_listing_number"})

m=t["listing_number"]/t["total_listing_number"]

t["rate"]=m

plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
sns.barplot(x="neighbourhood",y="rate",hue="room_type",data=t)
plt.xticks(rotation='90')
plt.ylabel('listing Number Rate', fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Nerighbourhood",fontsize=15)
plt.title('Map showing Count of Listing Type by Nerighbourhood ', fontsize=20)
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.04,1), loc="upper left")

Average price for each month¶

In [50]:
sns.set(style = "whitegrid")
x = month_price["month"]
y = month_price["price"]
z = month_price["price"]
cm = plt.cm.get_cmap('RdYlBu')
fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (10,8))
bubble = ax.scatter(x, y , s = (z - np.min(z) + 0.1) * 50, c = z, cmap = cm, linewidth = 0.5, alpha = 0.5)
ax.grid()
fig.colorbar(bubble)
ax.set_xlabel('month', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_ylabel('average price', fontsize = 15)
